There are two popular ways of security mechanisms exists

1) session based authentication
Limitations: session has to be replicated for applications running on multiple instances (redis shared cache). Or we need to sticky session
concept

server has to maintaing the state of the session id/token to identify the user

2) JWT  - based  authourization

A signed token will the handed over to the user he/she authenticated. Its users responsibilty to carry the signed token in the subsequent calls
